fragment_downloaded_cb({"url": "Python-module.html#find_installation", "fragment": "find_installation \nFind a python installation matching name_or_path. \nThat argument is optional if not provided then the returned python installation will be the one used to run meson. \nIf provided it can be \nA simple name eg python meson will look for an external program named that way using find_program \nA path eg usr local bin python3.4m \nOne of python2 or python3 in either case the module will try some alternative names py or py on Windows and python everywhere. In the latter case it will check whether the version provided by the sysconfig module matches the required major version \nKeyword arguments are the following \nReturns a python installation \n"});